notes.contentHTML:
I found a work around which might not be a good way. In index.html from the path given bellow, I changed the meta tag

node_modules > react-native-webview-quilljs > assets > index.html

from this

<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"/>

to

<meta name="viewport" content="initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0">

if there is any other solution, would be welcome

Ubiquiti


  1. Vad definierar bra ux/ui
  • UX - Seamless to use, user does not have to think when doing simple tasks
  • UI -
  1. The design must feel modern, what a modern design is is of course dependent on trends but when in comes to web development I think the most modern designs are the ones that really take advantage of the technologies that we have access to.
  2. The UX can't be compromised but the UI. What I mean by this is that even though the design is really important, if a user is distracted by, for instance, crazy animations and crazy video backgrounds the user will have a harder time to actually get the functionality out of the product.

  1. Vad är ett bra exempel på mjukvara/hårdvara? Varför tyckte du att den/det var bra?
  2. There is definitely one really important aspect of a products hardware and software and that is that they are kind of synched. I mean if we have a hardware which is insanely effecient and is able to do different cool things it would all be for nothing if we didn't attach it to an equally cool software which could manage all this functionality. It also aplies the other way around. Let's say that I develop a game for desktop computers. This game might have the best graphics that the gaming world has ever seen but if there are no graphic cards which are able to run it smoothly, this game will be useless.


  1.  Vad för typ av projekt/webbutveckling är du mest intresserad av/blir du mest exalterad av?
  2. My favourite projects to work on are definitely the ones which have a cool client that is attached to some kind of service. It's always satisfying to know how complex the different signals through the program might be. Let's say I have web client with a button that displays user data. It's a pretty simple task but for it to all work it requires this button to have some sort of event which triggers a request to be made to a service which in it's own turn receives the data from somewhere and then sends it back to the client for display.


  1. Hur hamnade du här (dvs på </salt>)? Berätta din story. Varför blev du intresserad av webbutveckling? Varför satsade du järnet på programmering?


  1. Var ser du dig själv om 5 år?
  2. In 5 years I see myself at a company having as much responsibility for a product as possible. The cool thing with beeing able to take executive decisions is that you can have as much impact on the product as possible. I will also always have the goal to improve myself at what I do. Every day I work as a developer I want to get better at it.
